			<p>We can expect "The Help" to turn up on Oscar night (Feb. 26) because Hollywood loves a winner, and a classy middlebrow success is the traditional definition of a winner. I hope a few of the pictures about to make their conspicuous debuts at the larger film festivals, notably Toronto, Venice and New York, turn out wonderfully so that we can talk about something other than "The Help" for a while.</p>
