			<p>It's not a matter of diminished ex- pectations to acknowledge the com- mercial film industry's Hippocratic Oath: First, do no boredom. It's simply acknowledging the pleasure the right diversion can deliver. If you get a little artistry out of it, terrific.</p>
			<p>Wouldn't it be nice if director Ste- ven Soderbergh's panic-stricken pan- demic thriller "Contagion" (opening Sept. 9) jangles our nerves and gets us thinking? And if director Bennett Miller's "Moneyball" (Brad Pitt as Beane) manages to transcend the well-meaning, "respectable" biopic genre loathed by Greene, I say: Atta film!</p>
